cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.DC, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper introduces a new logic language for specifying parametric architectures and models. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper discusses the modelling of software architectures with quantitative characteristics. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is another possible category as the paper deals with component-based systems and their interactions. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a possible category as the paper discusses the coordination of multiple components in a system. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a possible category as the paper deals with the design and specification of systems.
